org.identityconnectors.databasetable

Class DatabaseTableConfiguration

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.identityconnectors.framework.spi.AbstractConfiguration
      • org.identityconnectors.databasetable.DatabaseTableConfiguration
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Configuration

    public class DatabaseTableConfiguration
extends AbstractConfiguration
    Implements the Configuration interface to provide all the necessary parameters to initialize the JDBC Connector.

    • Field Detail

      • enableEmptyString

        public boolean enableEmptyString
        The empty string setting allow conversion of a null into an empty string for not-null char columns

      • rethrowAllSQLExceptions

        public boolean rethrowAllSQLExceptions
        Some database drivers will throw the SQLError when setting the parameters to the statement with zero ErrorCode. This mean no error. This switch allow to switch off ignoring this SQLError

      • nativeTimestamps

        public boolean nativeTimestamps
        Some JDBC drivers (ex: Oracle) may not be able to get correct string representation of TIMESTAMP data type of the column from the database table. To get correct value , one needs to use rs.getTimestamp() rather rs.getString().

      • allNative

        public boolean allNative
        Some JDBC drivers (ex: DerbyDB) may need to access all the datatypes with native types to get correct value.

        public boolean getSuppressPassword()
